Privacy Policy

This privacy policy explains how we collect, use, and protect your personal data when you use our Android app to chat with GPT (OpenAI's language model). By using our app, you agree to the collection and use of your data as described in this policy.

Data collection
We collect the following data when you use our app:

Chat messages: We collect the chat messages you send to GPT, which may include personal information.

Usage data: We collect data about how you use our app, such as your interactions with the chat interface and your device information.

Data use
We use the data we collect to:

Improve the performance of our app: We use your chat messages and usage data to improve the accuracy and responsiveness of GPT.

Personalize the user experience: We use your usage data to personalize the user experience of our app, such as by recommending relevant chat topics.

Third-party services
We use the following third-party services in our app:

Google Firebase: We use Firebase to provide cloud storage and analytics services for our app. Firebase collects data such as device information, app usage, and crash reports. For more information, please see Google's Privacy Policy.
Data retention
We retain your data for as long as it is necessary to provide our app services. We may also retain your data for a longer period if required by law or to protect our legal rights.

Data protection
We take appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect your data from unauthorized access or disclosure. We also regularly review and update our security practices to ensure the highest level of protection for your data.

Contact us
If you have any questions or concerns about your privacy, please contact us at adnanashraf.9011@gmail.com.

Updates
We may update this privacy policy from time to time to reflect changes in our data collection or data use practices. We encourage you to review this policy periodically to stay informed about our privacy practices
